SUMMARY:Natural Wine Tasting
DESCRIPTION:Natural Wine Tasting at Great Bear Vineyards in Davis \nSunday\, April 12 | 12–3pm\nCurious about natural wine? Come explore something beautifully different. Step into the world of Black Bicycle Farm’s natural\, orange\, and uniquely expressive wines—where minimal intervention lets nature take the lead and every glass tells a story. \nThis guided tasting is a journey through purity\, creativity\, and vineyard character\, perfect for both seasoned wine lovers and the naturally curious.\n What to Expect:\nA guided tasting of five distinct natural wines\nExplore orange wines\, unfiltered whites\, and vibrant reds\nLearn about carbonic maceration and low-intervention winemaking\nDiscover the philosophy behind letting nature shine in every bottle\n Featured Wines Include:\nSquiggle 2023 — bold\, textured orange wine with bright citrus layers\nOrange Tipple 2023 — floral and aromatic with apricot\, honey & orange notes\nClash of the Titans 2022 — a harmonious Cabernet Sauvignon–Zinfandel blend\nAfter the Fire 2020 — smoky\, spicy Cabernet with a powerful story\nCarbo Cab 2019 — playful\, unfiltered Cabernet bursting with cherry and strawberry\nSet against the rustic elegance of the vineyard\, this is your chance to sip\, learn\, and experience wines that are as thoughtful as they are delicious.\n Come discover something new\, sip something unexpected\, and enjoy a Sunday afternoon full of character at Great Bear Vineyards.
URL:https://visitdavis.org/event/natural-wine-tasting/
LOCATION:Great Bear Vineyards\, Great Bear Vineyards 24800 Co Rd 101A\, Davis\, CA 95616
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://visitdavis.org/wp-content/uploads/Great-Bear-Vineyards_23GBV-drone-scaled-zK0eUQ.jpg
ORGANIZER;CN="Great Bear Vineyards":MAILTO:greatbearvineyards@gmail.com
END:VEVENT
